abstract: Christopher Clarey On Tennis column highlights Novak Djokovic's victory over Rafael Nadal in men's quarterfinals at French Open tennis tournament; holds that feat should not be diminished because of Nadal's spotty play this season, considering Nadal has won French Open nine times.
lead_paragraph: Djokovic, the No. 1 seed, dominated Nadal, a nine-time French Open champion, a feat that should not be diminished by Nadal’s No. 7 ranking and spotty play this season.

headline.main: The Long Chase Is Over as Novak Djokovic Clobbers Rafael Nadal
